about.summary: A command line tool for interacting with cloud storage services.

name: gsutil
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "gsutil" %}
{% set version = "5.20" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0cb935f1fb14502f56e6100f93e43d9d7fa31822bc5ebffc932b7694b3fa08a9

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  entry_points:
    - gsutil = gslib.__main__:main
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - google-auth >=2.5.0
    - python >=3.6
    - argcomplete >=1.9.4
    - crcmod >=1.7
    - fasteners >=0.14.1
    - gcs-oauth2-boto-plugin >=3.0
    - google-apitools >=0.5.32
    - google-reauth >=0.1.0
    - httplib2 ==0.20.4
    - monotonic >=1.4
    - pyopenssl >=0.13
    - retry_decorator >=1.0.0
    - six >=1.12.0
  run_constrained:
    - google-cloud-sdk <0a

test:
  imports:
    - gslib
    - gslib.addlhelp
  commands:
    - pip check
    - gsutil version
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://pypi.org/project/gsutil/
  summary: A command line tool for interacting with cloud storage services.
  license: Apache-2.0
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xhochy
